# ============================================================================
# Example: Arpeggiator Patterns
# ============================================================================
#
# This example demonstrates:
# - Arpeggio patterns (broken chords played sequentially)
# - @loop for repetitive note sequences
# - Tempo changes for speed variation
#
# Arpeggio Theory:
# - Arpeggio = "broken chord" - chord tones played one at a time
# - Common patterns: up, down, up-down (triangle)
# - Creates rhythmic interest from static chords
#
# ============================================================================


# ============================================================================
# Pattern 1: Steady 8th Notes (C Major)
# ============================================================================

[00:00.000]
- marker "C Major Arpeggio"
- text "Steady eighth note arpeggio"
- tempo 120

@loop 32 times every 0.5b
  - note_on 1.C4 75 0.4b
@end


